editorialNotes.tagline: Holiday fun with a festive feline
editorialNotes.standard: The moment we met wee kitty Crumbs in Little Kitten, we let out an audible awww. This adorable digital feline encourages children to play and explore, interacting with the lively toys and simple games in Crumbs room. Were amazed by the cinematic animation, and appreciate the sleep timer that sends Crumbs to bed when our kids screen time is over.
editorialNotes.short: Embark on exciting adventures with your own kitty pal.

name: Hey Duggee The Big Outdoor App

editorialNotes.standard: See the beauty and power of ABCs in an app where every letter holds secret words. Touch an F, and it sprouts a foot, then feathers, then a fan; a G becomes a guitar in a garden with ghosts. Kids will love poking and prodding their way to the end of the alphabet, while parents will dig the unpredictability and gorgeous animation in this Apple Design Award winner.
editorialNotes.short: Interactive alphabet learning where words and letters come to life.

editorialNotes.tagline: Interact with the power of nature
editorialNotes.standard: Part digital toy and part planetary handbook, The Earth gives kids insight into the workings of our world in a way thats delightfully intuitive and fun. From rockslides to earthquakes to erupting volcanoes, these artful interactive dioramas respond to tapping and swiping with results that are both whimsical and educational. An accompanying guide for parents and teachers delves into the technical science behind all these phenomena, but kids can explore, experiment, and absorb earthly knowledge at their own pace.
editorialNotes.short: Play with interactive models to understand our planet.

editorialNotes.standard: Slide a shape into the correct holeeasy, right? It is, at first. But what makes Busy Shapes so clever is the way it gently gets more challenging, motivating little kids to find solutions to each puzzle through experimentation. From shape-changing to colour-mixing to hidden holes, were impressed with how the gameplay spurs out-of-the-box thinking, stimulating curious young minds.
